<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise ja olulise piiramise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Temporary Closure and Substantial Restriction of Railway Traffic </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse 6. detsembri 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rus nr 406 </eesti>
<inglise>Government of the Republic Regulation No. 406 of 6 December 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2000, 96, 619), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT (1) I 2000, 96, 619), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 16. detsembril 2000. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 16 December 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rus kehtestatakse "Raudteeseaduse" (RT I 1999, 29, 405) &sect; 23 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>This Regulation is established on the basis of subsection 23 (1) of the Railways Act (RT I 1999, 29, 405). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;te </eesti>
<inglise>General provision </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja, kes majandab avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteed (edaspidi raudtee), peab raudteeliikluse ajutisel sulgemisel kauemaks kui &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks (edaspidi raudteeliikluse ajutine sulgemine) v&otilde;i olulisel piiramisel j&auml;rgima k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korda. </eesti>
<inglise>A railway infrastructure manager who operates railway designated for public use (hereinafter railway) shall follow the procedure provided for in this Regulation upon temporary closure of railway traffic for longer than twenty-four hours (hereinafter temporary closure of railway traffic) or substantial restriction thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ajutine sulgemine ja oluline piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary closure and substantial restriction of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeliikluse ajutine sulgemine on &uuml;hel raudteel&otilde;igul mingiks ajaperioodiks k&otilde;igi liiklusgraafikus etten&auml;htud rongide k&auml;igust &auml;raj&auml;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Temporary closure of railway traffic means the cancellation of all scheduled trains in a railway section during a certain period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeliiklust piiratakse oluliselt, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Railway traffic is substantially restricted if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) j&auml;etakse kauemaks kui &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt k&auml;igust &auml;ra reisirongide s&otilde;iduplaanis etten&auml;htud rahvusvaheline v&otilde;i &uuml;hiskondliku veoteenuse osutamiseks kasutatav reisirong (edaspidi s&otilde;iduplaanis etten&auml;htud reisirong); </eesti>
<inglise>1) international passenger trains or passenger trains used for the provision of public transport services scheduled in the timetable of passenger trains (hereinafter scheduled passenger trains) are fully or partially cancelled for longer than twenty-four hours; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;hel raudteel&otilde;igul ei suudeta kauemaks kui &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks tagada liiklusgraafikus etten&auml;htud rongiliinidest rohkem kui kolme neljandiku kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the use of more than three fourths of scheduled train paths cannot be ensured in a railway section for longer than twenty-four hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui raudteeliikluse ajutisel sulgemisel v&otilde;i sellise piiramise rakendamisel, mille tagaj&auml;rjel j&auml;etakse t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt k&auml;igust &auml;ra s&otilde;iduplaanis etten&auml;htud reisirong v&otilde;i ei suudeta tagada liiklusgraafikus etten&auml;htud rongiliinidest rohkem kui kolme neljandiku kasutamist, ei ole ette teada rakendatud sulgemise v&otilde;i piiramise ajaline kestus &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evades, loetakse raudteeliiklus vastavalt kas ajutiselt suletuks kauemaks kui &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 m&otilde;istes oluliselt piiratuks, olenemata rakendatud sulgemise v&otilde;i piiramise tegelikust kestusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, upon temporary closure of railway traffic or restriction thereof as a result of which scheduled passenger trains are fully or partially cancelled or in case the use of more than three fourths of scheduled train paths cannot be ensured, the duration of closure or restriction in twenty-four hour periods is not known in advance, railway traffic shall be considered either temporarily closed for longer than twenty-four hours or substantially restricted within the meaning of subsection (2) of this section respectively, regardless of the actual duration of closure or restriction. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise eesm&auml;rk ja p&otilde;hjus </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of and reason for temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeliiklust v&otilde;ib ajutiselt sulgeda v&otilde;i oluliselt piirata "Raudteeseaduse" &sect; 16 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel kehtestatud raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas, "Raudteeseaduse" &sect; 17 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel kehtestatud raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja tegevuseeskirjas ja teistes &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud raudteeliiklusohutuse, keskkonnakaitse, tuleohutuse, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja muude n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise eesm&auml;rgil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway traffic may be temporarily closed or substantially restricted for the purpose of compliance with the requirements of railway safety, environmental protection, fire safety, occupational safety and other requirements provided for in the rules for technical use of railway established on the basis of subsection 16 (2) of the Railways Act, in the operating rules of railway infrastructure managers established on the basis of subsection 17 (1) of the Railways Act and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal teostatavad raudtee ehitus-, remondi- ja hooldust&ouml;&ouml;d (edaspidi raudteehoiut&ouml;&ouml;d) ning teised rakendatavad abin&otilde;ud peavad olema suunatud liiklusgraafikuj&auml;rgse raudteeliikluse taastamisele ja h&auml;ireteta ning ohutu raudteeliikluse tagamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Railway construction work, repair and maintenance services (hereinafter rail maintenance work) performed during temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic and other measures applied shall be taken with a view to restoring scheduled railway traffic and ensuring smooth and safe running of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeliiklus suletakse ajutiselt v&otilde;i seda piiratakse oluliselt, kui see on vajalik: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Railway traffic is temporarily closed or substantially restricted if it is necessary: </inglise>
<eesti>1) raudteehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) for the performance of rail maintenance work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) raudteeliiklusega raudteeinfrastruktuuri v&otilde;i raudteeveeremi tehnilise seisundi t&otilde;ttu inimeste elule v&otilde;i tervisele v&otilde;i keskkonnale tekkinud otsese ohu k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for the elimination of immediate hazard to human life or health or to the environment caused by railway traffic due to the technical state of railway infrastructure or rail vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>3) avariist, liiklus- v&otilde;i loodus&otilde;nnetusest, ilmastikuolude j&auml;rsust muutumisest v&otilde;i muust etten&auml;gematust asjaolust p&otilde;hjustatud erakorralise liiklustakistuse k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) for the removal of an extraordinary traffic obstruction caused by an accident, a traffic accident or natural disaster, sudden change in weather conditions or other unforeseen circumstances; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudel &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in other cases provided for by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Reisijatevedu raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of passengers during temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i sellise olulise piiramise ajal, mis toob kaasa &sect; 2 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 s&auml;testatud tagaj&auml;rje, on raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja kohustatud korraldama reisijateveo kogu rongiliini ulatuses v&otilde;i liiklustakistuse kohast m&ouml;&ouml;da teise transpordivahendiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) During temporary closure of railway traffic or substantial restriction thereof which brings about the consequence provided for in clause 2 (2) 1), a railway infrastructure manager is required to organise carriage of passengers in the full extent of the train path or past the traffic obstruction using other means of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui raudteeliikluse olulise piiramise p&otilde;hjuseks on raudteeliiklusega reisijateveoks kasutatava raudteeveeremi tehnilise seisundi t&otilde;ttu inimeste elule v&otilde;i tervisele v&otilde;i keskkonnale tekkinud otsese ohu k&otilde;rvaldamine, peab reisijateveo muu transpordivahendiga korraldama raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja, kelle raudteeveeremi tehniline seisund raudteeliikluse olulise piiramise p&otilde;hjustas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the reason for substantial restriction of railway traffic is the elimination of immediate hazard to human life or health or the environment caused by railway traffic due to the technical state of railway infrastructure or rail vehicles used for carriage of passengers, carriage of passengers using other means of transport shall be organised by the rail transport undertaking the technical state of whose rail vehicles is causing the substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest peab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja teatama Raudteeametile ja k&otilde;igile sellel raudteel raudteeveoteenust osutavatele raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele, kes raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal ei saa neile eraldatud rongiliine kasutada v&otilde;i saavad neid kasutada piiratult v&otilde;i teistsugustel tingimustel, kui on kokku lepitud raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamise lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A railway infrastructure manager shall give notification of a temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic to the Railway Administration and all rail transport undertakings providing rail transport services on the railway which, during the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic, cannot use the train paths allocated to them or can use the train paths to a restricted extent or under conditions different from the conditions agreed to in the contract for the use of railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>Teade edastatakse kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>Notification shall be in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud teates tuleb n&auml;idata raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise p&otilde;hjus, algus- ja l&otilde;ppt&auml;htaeg ning liikluskorraldus raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The notification provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall set out the reason for temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic, the terms of commencement and termination thereof and traffic control during the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Algus- ja l&otilde;ppt&auml;htaeg peavad olema m&auml;&auml;ratud kuup&auml;eva ja kellaajaga. </eesti>
<inglise>The terms of commencement and termination shall be determined as specified date and time. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui l&otilde;ppt&auml;htaeg ei ole kuup&auml;evaliselt ja kellaajaliselt ettem&auml;&auml;ratav, v&otilde;ib l&otilde;ppt&auml;htaja m&auml;&auml;rata s&uuml;ndmusega, mille saabumisel langeb &auml;ra raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise p&otilde;hjus. </eesti>
<inglise>If the term of termination cannot be determined as specified date and time in advance, the term of termination may be determined by an event at the arrival of which the reason for the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic ceases to exist. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui l&otilde;ppt&auml;htaeg on m&auml;&auml;ratud s&uuml;ndmusega, peab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja Raudteeametile ja raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele s&uuml;ndmuse saabumisest ja raudteeliikluse liiklusgraafikuj&auml;rgsest taastamisest t&auml;iendavalt teatama. </eesti>
<inglise>If the term for termination is determined by an event, the railway infrastructure manager shall give additional notification of the arrival of the event and restoration of scheduled railway traffic to the Railway Administration and rail transport undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudveoteenuse kasutajatele teatab raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjalt vastava teate saamisel raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the receipt of corresponding notification from a railway infrastructure manager, a rail transport undertaking shall notify users of rail transport services of a temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Teade edastatakse raudteeveoteenuse kasutajatele veoteenuse osutamiseks s&otilde;lmitud lepingus v&otilde;i veoeeskirjas s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Users of rail transport services shall be notified pursuant to the conditions and procedure provided for in the contract entered into for the provision of transport services or in transport regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>Informatsioon reisijateveo liikluskorralduse kohta raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal tuleb teha reisijatele k&auml;ttesaadavaks vastava rongiliini k&otilde;ikides peatuskohtades (raudteejaamades ja rongipeatustes). </eesti>
<inglise>Information concerning traffic control of carriage of passengers during the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic shall be made available to passengers at all stopping points in the corresponding train path (railway stations and railway stops). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teise riigi raudtee ja p&auml;devate organite ning vastavate rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonide teavitamisel raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest, samuti muudest liiklush&auml;iretest raudteel, mis on r&ouml;&ouml;pmelises otse&uuml;henduses teise riigi raudteega, ning kus raudteeliikluse ajutine sulgemine v&otilde;i oluline piiramine v&otilde;i muud liiklush&auml;ired toovad kaasa rahvusvahelise raudteeliikluse ajutise katkestuse v&otilde;i piiramise (edaspidi rahvusvahelise t&auml;htsusega raudtee), l&auml;htutakse vastavas rahvusvahelises kokkuleppes etten&auml;htud tingimustest ja korrast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Notification of railways and competent bodies of other countries and corresponding international organisations of temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic and of other traffic disturbances on railways directly connected to railways of other countries by track and where temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic or other traffic disturbances bring about temporary breakdown or restriction of international railway traffic (hereinafter railways of international importance) shall be guided by the conditions and procedure prescribed in the corresponding international agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest teatamise t&auml;htajad </eesti>
<inglise>Terms for notification of temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kavandatavast raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest riigisisese t&auml;htsusega raudteel teatab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja Raudteeametile ja raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele ette mitte v&auml;hem kui kaksk&uuml;mmend p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A railway infrastructure manager shall give notification of planned temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic on domestic railway to the Railway Administration and rail transport undertakings not less than twenty days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kavandatavast raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest rahvusvahelise t&auml;htsusega raudteel teatab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja Raudteeametile ette mitte v&auml;hem kui nelik&uuml;mmend kaheksa ja raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele ette mitte v&auml;hem kui nelik&uuml;mmend viis p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A railway infrastructure manager shall give notification of planned temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic on railway of international importance to the Railway Administration not less than forty-eight days and to rail transport undertakings not less than forty-five days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise tingivad erakorralised asjaolud, mis ei v&otilde;imalda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud etteteatamist&auml;htaegu j&auml;rgida, teatab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja Raudteeametile ja raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmisest v&otilde;i etteteatamise v&otilde;imatuse korral juba rakendatud raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic is caused by extraordinary circumstances which preclude observance of the terms for advance notice provided for in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, a railway infrastructure manager shall immediately give notification of the adoption of a decision of temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic or, if advance notification was impossible, temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic already in force to the Railway Administration and rail transport undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest Raudteeameti ettekirjutuse alusel teatab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele vastava ettekirjutuse saamisel ja Raudteeametile ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmisele asumisel viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A railway infrastructure manager shall give notification to rail transport undertakings of temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic pursuant to a precept of the Railway Administration upon the receipt of the corresponding precept and to the Railway Administration immediately upon commencing compliance with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Reisijatele teatab raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja kavandatavast raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest koos informatsiooni k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemisega reisijateveo liikluskorralduse kohta raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal mitte hiljem kui seitse p&auml;eva enne raudteeliikluse ajutist sulgemist v&otilde;i olulist piiramist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A rail transport undertaking shall notify passengers of planned temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic and make information concerning traffic control of carriage of passengers during the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic available not later than seven days prior to the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise tingivad erakorralised asjaolud, mis ei v&otilde;imalda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud etteteatamist&auml;htaega j&auml;rgida, peab raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja reisijatele raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjalt vastava teate saamisel raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest teatama ja informatsiooni raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajal rakendatava liikluskorralduse kohta k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegema viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic is caused by extraordinary circumstances which preclude observance of the term for advance notice provided for in subsection (5) of this section, a rail transport undertaking shall notify passengers of the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic upon receipt of the corresponding notice from the railway infrastructure manager and make information concerning traffic control implemented during the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic immediately available. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevuskava raudteeliikluse ajutisel sulgemisel v&otilde;i olulisel piiramisel </eesti>
<inglise>Action plan for temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koos teatega raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise kohta peab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja Raudteeametile esitama tegevuskava, kus tuleb n&auml;idata raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise ajaks kavandatud raudteehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ja muude rakendatavate abin&otilde;ude ning vastavalt &otilde;igusaktidele ning rahvusvahelistele kokkulepetele raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise korral t&auml;itmisele kuuluvate kohustuste loetelu ning teostamise t&auml;htajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Together with notice of a temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic, a railway infrastructure manager shall submit to the Railway Administration an action plan which sets out a list of rail maintenance works planned and other measures to be applied during the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic and obligations to be performed in the case of temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic pursuant to legislation and international agreements and terms for the performance thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui raudteeliikluse ajutise sulgemise v&otilde;i olulise piiramise tingivad erakorralised asjaolud, v&otilde;ib raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tegevuskava Raudteeametile esitada kolme p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast raudteeliikluse ajutisest sulgemisest v&otilde;i olulisest piiramisest teatamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic is caused by extraordinary circumstances, a railway infrastructure manager may submit the action plan provided for in subsection (1) of this section to the Railway Administration within three days as of notification of the temporary closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui raudteeliiklust piiratakse oluliselt reisijateveoks kasutatava raudteeveeremi tehnilise seisundi t&otilde;ttu, peab Raudteeametile tegevuskava s&otilde;iduplaanij&auml;rgse reisirongiliikluse taastamiseks esitama raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja, kelle raudteeveeremi tehniline seisund raudteeliikluse olulise piiramise p&otilde;hjustas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If substantial restriction of railway traffic is caused by the technical state of rail vehicles used for carriage of passengers, an action plan for restoring the scheduled traffic of passenger trains shall be submitted to the Railway Administration by the rail transport undertaking the technical state of whose rail vehicles is causing the substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevuskavas n&auml;idatakse s&otilde;iduplaanij&auml;rgse reisirongiliikluse taastamisele suunatud abin&otilde;ude loetelu ja nende rakendamise t&auml;htajad. </eesti>
<inglise>The action plan shall set out a list of measures directed at restoring the scheduled traffic of passenger trains and terms for the application thereof. </inglise>
